==Starting off==
===If the player hasn't cleared the Theatre before===
* '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Any luck in the Theatre?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|What am I meant to be doing again?}}
** '''Player:''' What am I meant to be doing again?
** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Enter the Theatre and beat the challenges within. Doing so would cause great embarrasment{{sic}} to Verzik, and my associates would very much appreciate it.
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|What's all this really about?}}
*** {{tact|below}}
** {{topt|quest=No|Can I get those teleport crystals you mentioned?}}
** {{topt|Okay, thanks.}}
*** '''Player:''' Okay, thanks.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|What's all this really about?}}
** '''Player:''' What's all this really about?
** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' What do you mean?
** '''Player:''' Well you don't really expect me to believe you're just here to embarrass Verzik do you? What's really going on?
** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' My associates prefer to keep their intentions to themselves. However, if you were to assist us with another matter, I might be able to share more.
** {{tselect|Start the A Night at the Theatre quest?}}
** {{topt|Yes.}}
*** '''Player:''' What do you need?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Your suspicions are correct. My role here is not to embarrass Verzik Vitur. Instead, my associates have a long history with Verzik, and have sent me here to keep an eye on her.
*** '''Player:''' So you're spying on her? Then why are you asking people to go and 'embarrass' her?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Research.
*** '''Player:''' Research?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Yes. As you're aware, of all those that go into the Theatre, the vast majority never come out. That said, some have managed to succeed. Of course, the vampyres would never let the citizens know this.
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Thanks to these successes, I've been able to gather information on Verzik and her abilities.
*** '''Player:''' Ah, so they're the ones that have been doing the spying. Still, that doesn't explain what this is all for.
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Verzik has abilities unlike any other vampyre. However, she did not always possess these abilities. My associates are keen to discover how she obtained them.
*** {{tcond|If the player has beaten Verzik before:}}
**** '''Player:''' You mean that thing she does where she turns into a spider?
**** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Exactly.
**** {{tact|continues}}
*** '''Player:''' Right, I think I understand now. So where do I come in?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' These were recently recovered from within the Theatre. Take a look at them.
*** {{tbox|pic=Nylocas queen eggs detail.png|The Mysterious Stranger shows you some eggs.}}
*** '''Player:''' Eggs?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Not just any eggs. These are the eggs of a nylocas, one of Verzik's arachnid pets.
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Normally this wouldn't be anything special. After all, Verzik has hundreds of nylocas. However, these eggs are from a variant we've never encountered before.
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' What's more interesting than that though is how they were obtained. For lack of a better description, the mercenary who recovered them claimed they 'fell out' of Verzik herself.
*** '''Player:''' Verzik laid some eggs?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Apparently so.
*** '''Player:''' How lovely. I think you've safely put me off my food for the rest of today. So you think these eggs are somehow connected to her unique abilities?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' It would line up with some suspicions my associates have had for a while.
*** {{tcond|If the player hasn't beaten Verzik before:}}
**** '''Player:''' And I suppose you want me to look into this?
**** {{tact|continues}}
*** {{tcond|If the player has beaten Verzik before:}}
**** '''Player:''' Not to mention the whole turning into a spider thing I guess. I suppose you want me to look into this?
**** {{tact|continues}}
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' That is correct. I also believe you have a friend who can help.
*** '''Player:''' I have a friend?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' A dead one.
*** '''Player:''' Ah, that sounds about right. Which dead friend are we talking about here?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Ranis Drakan.
*** '''Player:''' Right... And how's a dead vampyre going to help us exactly?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' My kind have the ability to relive our memories as if they are happening again. We can also relive the memories of others if we are able to make physical contact with them. I could show you if you want?
*** '''Player:''' Please don't go poking through my memories. Also, what do you mean by 'your kind'?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' I am not at liberty to say.
*** '''Player:''' Of course. How silly of me. And you want to relive Ranis' memories I'm guessing? Will that even work now that he's dead?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' We are lucky that vampyre corpses deteriorate slower than many other species. Enough of his brain should still be intact for me to work with.
*** '''Player:''' Err... Nice. What's he got to do with these eggs though?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Ranis and Verzik were close friends. He interacted with her more than anyone else did. Getting close enough to Verzik to observe her own memories will be... problematic. He is the next best option.
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Within his memories we can hopefully learn more about Verzik and her abilities. As for the eggs, they are our catalyst.
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' It would take years to search through all of Ranis' mind, but I can use these eggs to help us find relevant memories much faster.
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Now, I must remain here. That means you will need to recover Ranis for us.
*** '''Player:''' And where can I find him?
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Luckily for us, Ranis always loved the Theatre. As such, he is actually buried deep below it. You can use the staircase to the north east to access his crypt.
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Be careful, it's well guarded. Even other vampyres are not allowed in. I suggest you take that flail of yours.
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Also, you don't need to bring his whole body back of course. That wouldn't be very subtle. We only need his brain.
*** '''Player:''' Brains are generally attached to the body you know.
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' I know. That's why I'd recommend you take a saw.
*** '''Player:''' Oh... Oh god.
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Good luck.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|No.}}
*** '''Player:''' Actually, I'm not that interested.
*** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' As you wish. Return to me if you change your mind.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|quest=No|Can I get those teleport crystals you mentioned?}}
* {{topt|Not yet.}}
** '''Player:''' Not yet.
** '''Mysterious Stranger:''' Return to me when that changes.
** {{tact|end}}

